FullDescriptions:
Implementing the Sales and Distribution (SD) and Logistics Execution (LE) modules of the Global mySAP ERP system within Carmeuse, meaning:
Gather, define, & document business needs if the SD/LE modules to most efficiently meet these requirements;
Ensure Logistic Execution functionality for inter & intra company Stock Transfer Orders and Workflow for all modules;
Define user roles and develop detailed functional specifications for all customizations: forms, reports, interfaces, conversions, & enhancements.
Create and execute unit, string, and integration testing plans;
Record configuration settings and end user training document using approved documentation capture software;
Documenting business requirements and configuration settings;
Deliver end-user training;
Facilitating the change management process and end-user adoption of the SD/LE modules meaning: developing formal business cases, performing cost-benefit analysis and communicating features and benefits in non-technical terms;
Maintaining and supporting SAP SD/LE functionality being implemented. Analyze and correct problems as they occur in production;
Provide global helpdesk support for ongoing business needs;
Requirements
Bachelor’s degree in Business, Information Technology, a related field, or equivalent work experience. Advanced degree preferred;
Experience with 2 Full Life Cycle Implementations (less with multiple rollouts);
Experience with the full project life cycles of the SAP ERP system i.e. scoping, planning, designing, building, testing, and go-live;
3 years of SAP programming/configuration experience with the Sales and Distribution and Logistics Execution modules;
Versed in ASAP methodology;
Mid-level experience in the configuration and use of master data, sales order processing (quotes, sales orders, billing), shipment and shipment cost documents, routs, pricing, and stock transfer orders;
Good knowledge of SAP structures, configuration standards, transport protocols, object dependencies and tables, and security authorization;
Business aptitude in the discipline(s) relevant to the Sales and Distribution and Logistics Execution modules
Fluent in English (written & spoken)
Open to travel (+/- 30%)
READY TO JOIN A ROCK-SOLID FAMILY?
Carmeuse started out as a small family-run business in Belgium.
Today it’s a leading global producer of lime, high calcium limestone and dolomitic stone. Its products are essential to energy producers, environmental services, construction and manufacturing.
With over 90 production facilities spread across almost every continent, and over 4,500 employees working at Carmeuse every day, the company’s most treasured resources are its people.
You will be part of Carmeuse Americas, a Rock-Star team of 2500 workers and employees bringing with them their own culture and specific needs. The Americas headquarters are located in Pittsburgh, PA and have over three dozen production facilities across the Eastern U.S., Canada, Chile, Brazil, and Colombia.
